===Etymology===
{{enm}} [[wargeld]], from [[w:Old English language|Old English]][[category:Words of Old English language origin]] [[ƿergeld]], compound of [[ƿer]], ''man'' + [[geld]], ''payment''.

===Noun===
'''wergeld'''
# In Anglo-Saxon and Germanic law, a reparational payment usually demanded of a person guilty of homicide or other serious crimes.

